'''''Jedi Men From Baronis''''' was a [[Jediboh Opera]] play written by Master Thespian [[Damien Tantrellius]], who also played the leading role. It brought him fame when he played it on [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]] and was about confused identities when two traveling [[Bantha/Legends|bantha]] salesmen were mistakenly thought to be [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] and were thus forced to defend a small village from [[Isorpian Raiders]]. However, during the play, the bantha salesmen encountered a real [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]], who saved them while he attempted to hide his true identity.

It had a sequel, ''[[Two Jedi Men From Baronis]]''.

